OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772447794
OL,3,CRat activity shows significant
OL,4,Cincrease after hot summer and recent
OL,5,Crain
OL,7,FRat activity in UK properties has
OL,8,Fsignificantly increased over the last
OL,9,Fyear, thought to be due to a record
OL,10,Fhot summer and exacerbated by recent
OL,11,Fwet weather.
OL,13,FRentokil Pest Control said it had
OL,14,Frecorded a 10% year-on-year increase
OL,15,Fin confirmed rodent activity, with
OL,16,Flarge regional spikes in Northern
OL,17,FIreland and northern England.
OL,19,FNorthern Ireland recorded the largest
OL,20,Fincrease of 26%, followed by Yorkshire
OL,21,F(20%) and north-west England (19%).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772447794
OL,3,CRat activity shows significant
OL,4,Cincrease after hot summer and recent
OL,5,Crain
OL,7,FSeveral other regions, including the
OL,8,FWest Midlands (16%) and Scotland
OL,9,F(14%), also had double-digit rises.
OL,11,FRentokil said longer-term climate
OL,12,Fpatterns could be contributing to the
OL,13,Fincrease, including 2025 being the
OL,14,FUK's warmest year on record.
OL,16,FIt said milder weather could increase
OL,17,Frat reproduction by extending their
OL,18,Fbreeding season and leading to larger
OL,19,Fpopulations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
