FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772447794
OL,3,CRat activity shows significant
OL,4,Cincrease after hot summer and recent
OL,5,Crain
OL,7,FPaul Blackhurst, from Rentokil, said:
OL,8,F"Rats are highly capable swimmers.
OL,9,FThey can navigate strong currents,
OL,10,Fenter exposed pipes and sewers, and
OL,11,Fswim considerable distances in open
OL,12,Fwater.
OL,14,F"However, what they cannot tolerate is
OL,15,Fprolonged submersion. When burrow
OL,16,Fsystems and sewer networks flood, rats
OL,17,Fare forced to seek higher, drier
OL,18,Fground, increasing the risk of
OL,19,Finfestations in properties.
OL,26,@pD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
