CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772447794
OL,3,CRat activity shows significant
OL,4,Cincrease after hot summer and recent
OL,5,Crain
OL,7,FAfter periods of heavy rain, storms
OL,8,Fand flooding, property owners are
OL,9,Fadvised to take proactive steps to
OL,10,Freduce the risk of rodent activity,
OL,11,Fincluding:
OL,13,F` Clearing debris promptly by removing
OL,14,Ffallen branches, leaves and other
OL,15,Fitems that may have accumulated around
OL,16,Fthe property, as these create ideal
OL,17,Fhiding and nesting spots for rats.
OL,19,F` Sealing potential entry points.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1772447794
OL,3,CRat activity shows significant
OL,4,Cincrease after hot summer and recent
OL,5,Crain
OL,7,F` Inspecting the walls and foundations
OL,8,Fof the property for gaps, as rats can
OL,9,Fsqueeze through "surprisingly small"
OL,10,Fopenings.
OL,12,F` Removing sources of food by ensuring
OL,13,Foutdoor bins are sturdy, fitted with
OL,14,Ftight lids and positioned away from
OL,15,Fbuilding walls where possible.
